WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.689
Nightcap. Sunday, April twenty-sixth, twenty twenty-six. A shooting at the White House

00:00:02.689 --> 00:00:05.379
Correspondents' Dinner is the news story the morning briefing didn't have. The

00:00:05.379 --> 00:00:08.068
Hormuz markets twitched in two directions at once. Bloomberg dropped a Cook-to-Ternus

00:00:08.068 --> 00:00:10.758
pipeline piece that's the first real read of the post-Cook Apple roadmap.

00:00:10.758 --> 00:00:13.447
Katelyn sent you an Anthropic Greenhouse posting unprompted. And the Whoop decision

00:00:13.447 --> 00:00:16.136
finally landed. "Agree. Is the life really worth the extra?" That last

00:00:16.136 --> 00:00:18.826
one is the one to sit with. The Scorecard. What moved between

00:00:18.826 --> 00:00:21.515
this morning's pull and nine ten P-M Central. Anthropic greater than OpenAI

00:00:21.515 --> 00:00:24.205
twenty twenty-six on Manifold went from fifty-eight point two-eight percent this morning

00:00:24.205 --> 00:00:26.894
to fifty-eight point eight-one percent tonight. Up half a point. First activity

00:00:26.894 --> 00:00:29.583
in days, but only sixty mana of twenty-four-hour volume. The Hormuz Normal

00:00:29.583 --> 00:00:32.273
by April thirtieth Polymarket mirror went from one point zero percent to

00:00:32.273 --> 00:00:34.962
one point one zero percent, basically flat — pure resolution noise with

00:00:34.962 --> 00:00:37.652
five days to close. Hormuz Normal by end of May went from

00:00:37.652 --> 00:00:40.341
thirty-four percent up to thirty-seven point nine three percent — that's a

00:00:40.341 --> 00:00:43.030
re-bid of nearly four points, almost reversing Saturday's drop. Hormuz Normal by

00:00:43.030 --> 00:00:45.720
end of June went the other way, from fifty-eight percent down to

00:00:45.720 --> 00:00:48.409
fifty-five percent — gave back the overnight gain. The Trump-announces-blockade-lifted-by-April-thirtieth contract went

00:00:48.409 --> 00:00:51.099
from eight point eight percent up to eleven percent — plus two

00:00:51.099 --> 00:00:53.788
point two on substantive forty-two-hundred-mana volume. Sixty ships transit by April thirtieth

00:00:53.788 --> 00:00:56.477
basically flat at four percent. Read the table. The Iran complex moved

00:00:56.477 --> 00:00:59.167
in two directions at once today, which is more interesting than yesterday's

00:00:59.167 --> 00:01:01.856
clean down-bid. The end-of-May market clawed back almost everything it lost on

00:01:01.856 --> 00:01:04.546
Saturday. The end-of-June market gave back almost everything it bid in overnight.

00:01:04.546 --> 00:01:07.235
The two together say: bettors got more optimistic about the next five

00:01:07.235 --> 00:01:09.924
weeks and less optimistic about the nine-week tail. That's a coherent re-read

00:01:09.924 --> 00:01:12.614
of "phone diplomacy might produce a process before the end of May,

00:01:12.614 --> 00:01:15.303
but probably not a return to baseline by end of June." The

00:01:15.303 --> 00:01:17.992
Trump-blockade-lifted contract quietly added two point two points on real volume —

00:01:17.992 --> 00:01:20.682
that's the cleanest single-direction move of the day, and it's the market

00:01:20.682 --> 00:01:23.371
most directly tied to a Trump tweet that says, "OK, lift it."

00:01:23.371 --> 00:01:26.061
The Anthropic-greater-than-OpenAI market finally registered some activity. Sixty mana of twenty-four-hour volume

00:01:26.061 --> 00:01:28.750
is small — you wouldn't read a single trader's trade as a

00:01:28.750 --> 00:01:31.439
re-rate — but it's the first touch on this market since Friday

00:01:31.439 --> 00:01:34.129
morning. The number ticked up to fifty-eight point eight one. Sub-one-point drift,

00:01:34.129 --> 00:01:36.818
but the silence is broken. The real read is still Monday's open

00:01:36.818 --> 00:01:39.508
with full New York volume. Tonight is just the audible click of

00:01:39.508 --> 00:01:42.197
the door coming unstuck. The Plot Thickens. Three morning stories that genuinely

00:01:42.197 --> 00:01:44.886
developed today. Two of them were promised in the morning briefing as

00:01:44.886 --> 00:01:47.576
"things to watch," and they delivered. Iran. The markets repriced into the

00:01:47.576 --> 00:01:50.265
diplomatic ambiguity, not against it. The morning briefing pegged Trump's framing —

00:01:50.265 --> 00:01:52.955
"if they want to talk, they can call" — as deliberately ambiguous,

00:01:52.955 --> 00:01:55.644
leaving room for re-engagement without a public reversal. The evening Manifold tape

00:01:55.644 --> 00:01:58.333
says bettors believed the ambiguity was real. The Trump-announces-blockade-lifted contract is the

00:01:58.333 --> 00:02:01.023
cleanest read of "Trump says OK and pulls the boats" probability, and

00:02:01.023 --> 00:02:03.712
it added two point two points today on the heaviest twenty-four-hour volume

00:02:03.712 --> 00:02:06.402
of any Iran market on the board. End-of-May Hormuz-normal moved with it.

00:02:06.402 --> 00:02:09.091
That's not "the diplomatic track is back" — both markets are still

00:02:09.091 --> 00:02:11.780
well below their pre-collapse levels — but it is "the door isn't

00:02:11.780 --> 00:02:14.470
sealed shut, and bettors are pricing the small possibility that Trump tweets

00:02:14.470 --> 00:02:17.159
the climbdown himself." The end-of-June fade is the counterweight: the market still

00:02:17.159 --> 00:02:19.849
expects the blockade as a structurally durable feature into the summer. Translation:

00:02:19.849 --> 00:02:22.538
short tail more open, long tail more closed. What still hasn't moved:

00:02:22.538 --> 00:02:25.227
no formal ceasefire end, no Lloyd's revision, no M-S-C or Greek-operator I-M-O

00:02:25.227 --> 00:02:27.917
escalation. The structural state remains where it was twelve hours ago. The

00:02:27.917 --> 00:02:30.606
market is moving on tone, not facts. Apple. Bloomberg's Gurman shipped the

00:02:30.606 --> 00:02:33.296
Ternus roadmap piece you'd been waiting for. Sunday's Power On — out

00:02:33.296 --> 00:02:35.985
today, recapped on Reddit's r-slash-Apple at six hundred sixty upvotes — is

00:02:35.985 --> 00:02:38.674
titled, "Apple's Cook Gives Ternus a Pipeline of Ten Major New Product

00:02:38.674 --> 00:02:41.364
Categories." The framing is Cook handing over a stocked roadmap, foldable iPhone

00:02:41.364 --> 00:02:44.053
named as Ternus's first major product, ten categories deep. It's the first

00:02:44.053 --> 00:02:46.743
real Ternus-era story that isn't just speculation about which silicon person Ternus

00:02:46.743 --> 00:02:49.432
is. It changes the foldable-iPhone-twenty-twenty-six market read: that contract sat at eighty-five

00:02:49.432 --> 00:02:52.121
percent all weekend, and Gurman's "Ternus's first major product is the foldable"

00:02:52.121 --> 00:02:54.811
